This article summarizes President Trump's remarks during a visit to Fort Lauderdale, Florida after the recent school shooting. He thanked the first responders and medical professionals for their incredible work, and expressed his gratitude to Governor Rick Scott and Attorney General Pam Bondi for their support. Various officials and law enforcement officers also spoke, sharing their experiences and thanking the President for his visit. The First Lady emphasized the importance of taking care of the children affected by the tragedy. Sheriff Israel thanked the President for his support and mentioned a touching moment when the President and First Lady spent time with the son of an injured deputy.